        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">utf8proc_map() can return a NULL-pointer if it fails, which we would need to handle. \r\n\r\nYou can't imagine how relieved I am to read this. I was trying to figure out what regexp.c does and the only thing I managed to understand was that I don't have nearly enough IQ points to understand anything else.\r\n\r\nI can confirm that\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/mbyte.c b/src/nvim/mbyte.c\r\nindex 0c1b537f3a..bb5b8b0e63 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/mbyte.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/mbyte.c\r\n@@ -1311,6 +1311,10 @@ int utf_fold(int a)\r\n   utf8proc_map((utf8proc_uint8_t *)input_str, 0, &fold_str_utf,\r\n                UTF8PROC_NULLTERM | UTF8PROC_CASEFOLD);\r\n \r\n+  if (fold_str_utf == NULL) {\r\n+    return a;\r\n+  }\r\n+\r\n   int fold_codepoint_utf = utf_ptr2char((char *)fold_str_utf);\r\n \r\n   xfree(fold_str_utf);\r\n```\r\nSeems to make the problem go away, although I don't know if that's a proper fix or not.",
